## Key Screen Specifications

### Host Game View (`/host/game/[gameId]`)
Layout (desktop `lg:`): Three-column grid
- **Left panel:** Player count, round info (pattern name, prize, pattern visualizer), round controls
- **Center panel:** Large current number display, call history (last 5 numbers)
- **Right panel:** Full 75-number caller grid (tappable buttons)

Layout (mobile): Stacked vertically — current number → called history → round info → number grid

Number caller grid:
- 5 columns (B/I/N/G/O), 15 rows each
- Column header styled with its column color variable
- Called numbers: filled with `--accent-secondary`, non-interactive appearance
- Uncalled: outlined, tappable
- Hover state: subtle glow matching column color

### Player Game View (`/play/[gameId]`)
- Top: Large current number ball (animated on update)
- Below: Called numbers grid — compact, color-coded by column
- Bottom sticky bar: Round info (pattern name, prize if set, round X of Y)
- Connection status indicator (top-right corner)

### Game Setup (`/host/create`)
- Multi-step form: Step 1 (rounds count) → Step 2 (per-round config) → Step 3 (review + create)
- Per-round config: pattern selector with visual preview, optional prize text field
- Progress indicator at top

### Join Screen (`/play`)
- Centered, clean layout
- Large code input with auto-uppercase, auto-focus
- Support for URL param: `/play?code=ABC123` auto-fills the field
- Subtle animated background (slow-moving gradient or particle field)

---

## Component Implementation Rules

### General
- All components are typed with TypeScript — no `any`
- Use `"use client"` only when necessary (interactivity, hooks, browser APIs)
- Server Components by default in the App Router
- All async data fetching in Server Components or custom hooks
- Export types alongside components when they might be reused

### Styling
- Tailwind utility classes only — no inline `style={{}}` except for dynamic CSS variable values
- Use `cn()` (from `lib/utils.ts` via shadcn) for conditional class merging
- Column colors applied via `style={{ color: 'var(--col-b)' }}` pattern for dynamic column mapping
- Dark theme throughout — no light mode toggle needed for MVP

### shadcn/ui Usage
- Use shadcn primitives for: Dialog, Sheet, Button, Input, Select, Badge, Tooltip, Toast
- Customize via Tailwind and CSS variables, not by forking component internals
- Keep `components/ui/` untouched (shadcn managed); extend via wrapper components

### Framer Motion
- Wrap animated lists with `AnimatePresence` for enter/exit
- Use `layout` prop on reordering lists
- Keep animation configs in a shared `lib/animations.ts` constant file
- Example number ball animation:
```typescript
const numberBallVariants = {
  initial: { scale: 0.7, opacity: 0 },
  animate: { scale: 1, opacity: 1, transition: { type: "spring", stiffness: 300, damping: 20 } },
  exit: { scale: 0.8, opacity: 0 },
};
```

---

## Auth & Route Protection

```typescript
// middleware.ts
export const config = {
  matcher: ["/host/:path*"],
};
// Redirect unauthenticated users from /host/* to /login
```

- Hosts: email/password Firebase Auth
- Players: Firebase anonymous auth (auto sign-in on join)
- `useAuth` hook exposes `{ user, loading, isHost }`
- `isHost` = user exists AND is not anonymous

---

## Firestore Security Rules

```javascript
rules_version = '2';
service cloud.firestore {
  match /databases/{database}/documents {

    match /users/{userId} {
      allow read, write: if request.auth.uid == userId;
    }

    match /games/{gameId} {
      allow read: if request.auth != null;
      allow create: if request.auth != null && !request.auth.token.firebase.sign_in_provider.matches('anonymous');
      allow update, delete: if request.auth.uid == resource.data.hostId;

      match /calledNumbers/{numberId} {
        allow read: if request.auth != null;
        allow write: if request.auth.uid == get(/databases/$(database)/documents/games/$(gameId)).data.hostId;
      }

      match /players/{playerId} {
        allow read: if request.auth != null;
        allow create: if request.auth.uid == playerId;
        allow update: if request.auth.uid == playerId;
      }
    }
  }
}
```

---

## Error Handling

- All Firebase operations wrapped in try/catch with user-facing toast messages
- Network disconnection: show a persistent banner ("Reconnecting...") using Firestore's `onSnapshotsInSync` / metadata
- Invalid game code: clear inline error on the join form
- Host tries to call a number already called: silently ignore (idempotent)
- Game not found: redirect to `/play` with an error toast

