## Code Quality Rules

- **TypeScript:** strict mode, no implicit `any`, explicit return types on all functions
- **Imports:** absolute imports via `@/` alias (configured in `tsconfig.json`)
- **No magic numbers:** constants in `lib/constants.ts` (e.g., `MAX_ROUNDS = 10`, `GAME_CODE_LENGTH = 6`)
- **Async:** always handle loading and error states — never assume success
- **Comments:** explain *why*, not *what*; complex Firestore queries and real-time logic deserve comments
- **File naming:** `PascalCase` for components, `camelCase` for hooks/utils, `kebab-case` for route segments
- **Barrel exports:** each feature folder exports from an `index.ts`

---

## Performance

- Firestore listeners: always unsubscribe in `useEffect` cleanup
- Memoize expensive computations (e.g., splitting 75 numbers into columns) with `useMemo`
- `next/font` for zero-layout-shift font loading
- Images (QR codes, etc.) via `next/image`
- Avoid unnecessary re-renders: Zustand slices, `React.memo` on pure display components like `NumberBall`

---

## What Was Migrated From Flutter

This app was originally built in Flutter with Firebase. The data model, Firestore structure, and core game logic are preserved exactly. Only the presentation layer changes:

| Flutter | Next.js Equivalent |
|---|---|
| `Provider` / `Riverpod` | Zustand + React hooks |
| `StreamBuilder` | `useEffect` + `onSnapshot` |
| `Navigator` | Next.js App Router |
| `firebase_messaging` | Removed for MVP (no push notifications) |
| `qr_flutter` | `qrcode.react` npm package |
| `responsive_framework` | Tailwind responsive prefixes |
| Flutter widgets | React components + shadcn/ui |

Push notifications are explicitly out of scope for the initial web migration and will be revisited in a later phase.
